%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grind, to mill"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَحَنَ (ṭaḥana) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flour"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṭaḥan- (“to grind, crush”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒁲𒂊𒉡𒌝 (ṭênum) and Biblical Hebrew טָחַן (ṭɔḥan)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.ħa.na/","/tˤaħn/","/tˤiħn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26428","headword_ar":"طَحْنٌ","root":"THn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26429","headword_ar":"طِحْنٌ","root":"THn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHiynN","text_ar":"طَحِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and sometimes the inf. n., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHonN","text_ar":"طَحْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is used in this sense. (Msb.) Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEu","text_ar":"اَسْمَعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEojaEapF walaA A^araY TiHonFA","text_ar":"جَعْجَعَةً وَلَا اَرَى طِحْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hear a sound of the mill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mill-stone, but I see not flour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["MA"]},{"entry_id":"n26430","headword_ar":"طُحَنٌ","root":"THn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain small creeping thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwayob~apN","text_ar":"دُوَيْبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in form like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the species of lizard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reptile, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~ Hubayon","text_ar":"اُمّ حُبَيْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", [see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbn","text_ar":"حبن"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but more slender"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloTafu","text_ar":"اَلْطَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than this latter, that raises its tail like as does the pregnant camel, and, when bidden to grind, by the children of the Arabs of the desert, grinds with itself the ground until it becomes concealed in the soft soil; and one never sees it but in a tract of ground such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~uwqap","text_ar":"بَلُّوقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": Az says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuHanapN","text_ar":"طُحَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain small creeping thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwyb~p","text_ar":"دويبّة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beetle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juEal","text_ar":"جُعَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuHanN","text_ar":"طُحَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl.: [but, properly speaking, the latter is a coll. gen. n., and the former is the n. un.:] As says that it is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a creature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smaller than the hedge-hog, that comes into existence in the sands, appearing sometimes, and turning round as though grinding, and then diving"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAnapN","text_ar":"عَوَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and, (K,) accord. to Aboo-Kheyreh, (TA,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuHan","text_ar":"طُحَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovu Eifir~iyna","text_ar":"لَيْثُ عِفِرِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efr","text_ar":"عفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovu Eiforiyna","text_ar":"لَيْثُ عِفْرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the pistachio-nut, in colour like the dust, that buries itself in the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Short:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [or] accord. to Zj, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuHanapN","text_ar":"طُحَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short, having in him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luwvap","text_ar":"لُوثَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stupidity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and IB says that he who is tall, having in him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lwvp","text_ar":"لوثة"},{"kind":"text","text":", is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EusoqudN","text_ar":"عُسْقُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short in the utmost degree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) accord. to IKh, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shortest of the short;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the tallest of the tall is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaro TuwlN","text_ar":"سَمَرْ طُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Az"]}]}}